strings.Value: "Show me what you have for sale."
"Tessie, do you have any books by Willas Gunderson?"
{n}The plump book peddler gives you a gap-toothed grin.{/n} "Good day, Your 'Ighness!"
"For now, for now. Linzi wants my help selling the books she's printing. Trade's good, so I'll stick around and be an eyesore for a while. When I'm tired of it, I'll be on my way!"
"Nothing to tell! Native of nowhere, live on the road, peddle books... No family, no home — no cares, no troubles!"
"A good day to ya! Take care of Linzi!"

"Pardon me, Your 'Ighness! I once took a couple of his books with me, and I dragged 'em around for three years till someone bought 'em for a pittance as kindling. Won't be easy to finding the works of that scribbler. Maybe someone in town has some."
"Damn wretches! I'll get you! Oh, I'm sorry, Your 'Ighness, I didn't mean you..."
"Them thieves! Came and stole a few new books from me. Then left a note, of all things — 'Stolen by the brothers and a sister of Zottenropple, best wishes!' The impudence!"
